This paper is primarily focused on the design and implementation of a machine learning-based approach for configuring programmable wireless environments. As such, it is likely to fall under the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of software-defined metasurfaces (SDMs) and their control over surface currents, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) categories. The use of machine learning for configuring SDMs also implies that the paper may be relevant to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of programmable wireless environments in multimedia communication, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the Multimedia (cs.MM) category.
